    "body": "Care to respond? Note also that using Substrate in implementations may increase time to main net (or may not if starting from scratch) but has advantages such as modularity, flexibility, integration of Wasm, libp2p, GRANDPA consensus, blockchain interoperability, automatic upgradability and governance. And yes while I recognize that automatic upgradability may have issues around disenfranchising node operators from governance, having it as an option to experiment with using Sybil resistant methods seems beneficial. Having modularity with Substrate makes it easier to experiment, deploy new testnets and main nets, etc.",
