    "created_at": "2019-02-08T19:53:23Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-02-08T19:53:23Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Parity is currently building a 2.0 client in substrate. Although the promise of using substrate is high, they have had to make a few modifications to the underlying framework to accommodate for the 2.0 design (for example, being able to evaluate fork choice at slot boundaries rather than just when receiving a block).\r\n\r\nI have not done a deep dive on GRANDPA but FFG and GRANDPA satisfy many of the same design goals -- finality gadget on top of a chain, safety under asynchrony, and plausible liveness. FFG is well studied and understood by the protocol researchers designing 2.0 and is already integrated into the spec. I don't expect the consensus algorithm at this point to change without a powerful argument.\r\n\r\nIt is far more likely that we switch the consensus algorithm to a different family with more desirable properties in the long term rather than switching from FFG to another finality gadget. For example, CBC for the beacon chain is under R&D, and looks promising in resolving issues that arise between the finality gadget and the fork choice.\r\n",
